Document: XMLParser
Path: godot/classes/class_xmlparser.rst
Summary: Provides methods for parsing XML data.

XMLParser

Inherits: Object < Object

A low-level XML parser.

This class provides methods for parsing XML data. It is a low-level parser, meaning it does not automatically build a tree structure of the XML document. Instead, it allows you to iterate through the XML nodes and process them as you see fit. This can be more memory-efficient for very large XML files.

Methods:
open_buffer(buffer: PackedByteArray) → int
Opens an XML document from a byte array. Returns an error code.
open_file(path: String) → int
Opens an XML document from a file path. Returns an error code.
read(reuse_nodes: bool = false) → int
Reads the next node from the XML document. Returns an error code.
skip(reuse_nodes: bool = false) → int
Skips the current node and its children. Returns an error code.
next(reuse_nodes: bool = false) → int
Moves to the next node. Returns an error code.
get_node_type() → int
Returns the type of the current node.
get_node_name() → StringName
Returns the name of the current node.
get_node_data() → String
Returns the data of the current node.
get_attribute_count() → int
Returns the number of attributes for the current node.
get_attribute_name(idx: int) → StringName
Returns the name of the attribute at the given index.
get_attribute_value(idx: int) → String
Returns the value of the attribute at the given index.
has_attribute(name: StringName) → bool
Checks if the current node has an attribute with the given name.
get_attribute_value_by_name(name: StringName) → String
Returns the value of the attribute with the given name.
is_valid() → bool
Checks if the parser is currently in a valid state.
get_error_line() → int
Returns the line number where the last error occurred.
get_error_message() → String
Returns the error message for the last error.

