---CHUNK---
Document: XMLParser
Path: godot/classes/class_xmlparser.rst
Summary: Provides a low-level interface for creating parsers for XML files, serving as a base for custom XML parsers.
Inherits: RefCounted

Provides a low-level interface for creating parsers for XML files. This class can serve as a base to make custom XML parsers.

To parse XML, you must open a file with the open() method or a buffer with the open_buffer() method. Then, the read() method must be called to parse the next nodes. Most of the methods take into consideration the currently parsed node.

Here is an example of using XMLParser to parse an SVG file (which is based on XML), printing each element and its attributes as a dictionary:

GDScript:
    var parser = XMLParser.new()
    parser.open("path/to/file.svg")
    while parser.read() != ERR_FILE_EOF:
        if parser.get_node_type() == XMLParser.NODE_ELEMENT:
            var node_name = parser.get_node_name()
            var attributes_dict = {}
            for idx in range(parser.get_attribute_count()):
                attributes_dict[parser.get_attribute_name(idx)] = parser.get_attribute_value(idx)
            print("The ", node_name, " element has the following attributes: ", attributes_dict)

C#:
    var parser = new XmlParser();
    parser.Open("path/to/file.svg");
    while (parser.Read() != Error.FileEof)
    {
        if (parser.GetNodeType() == XmlParser.NodeType.Element)
        {
            var nodeName = parser.GetNodeName();
            var attributesDict = new Godot.Collections.Dictionary();
            for (int idx = 0; idx < parser.GetAttributeCount(); idx++)
            {
                attributesDict[parser.GetAttributeName(idx)] = parser.GetAttributeValue(idx);
            }
            GD.Print($"The {nodeName} element has the following attributes: {attributesDict}");
        }
    }
---CHUNK---
Document: XMLParser
Path: godot/classes/class_xmlparser.rst
Summary: This chunk covers the XMLParser class methods and the NodeType enumeration used to identify XML node types during parsing.

Enumeration: NodeType
- NODE_NONE (0): No node (no file or buffer opened).
- NODE_ELEMENT (1): An element node type (tag), e.g., <title>.
- NODE_ELEMENT_END (2): An end of element node type, e.g., </title>.
- NODE_TEXT (3): A text node type, including whitespace not inside an element.
- NODE_COMMENT (4): A comment node type, e.g., <!--A comment-->.
- NODE_CDATA (5): A node type for CDATA sections, e.g., <![CDATA[CDATA section]]>.
- NODE_UNKNOWN (6): An unknown node type.

Method: get_attribute_count() → int
Returns the number of attributes in the currently parsed element. Note: If the current node is not NODE_ELEMENT or NODE_ELEMENT_END, this count will not be updated and will reflect the last element.

Method: get_attribute_name(idx: int) → String
Returns the name of an attribute of the currently parsed element at the specified index.

Method: get_attribute_value(idx: int) → String
Returns the value of an attribute of the currently parsed element at the specified index.

Method: get_current_line() → int
Returns the current line in the parsed file, counting from 0.

Method: get_named_attribute_value(name: String) → String
Returns the value of an attribute of the currently parsed element by name. Raises an error if the attribute does not exist.

Method: get_named_attribute_value_safe(name: String) → String
Returns the value of an attribute of the currently parsed element by name. Returns an empty string if the attribute does not exist.

Method: get_node_data() → String
Returns the contents of a text node. Raises an error if the current node is not a text node.

Method: get_node_name() → String
Returns the name of a node. Raises an error if the current node is a text node. Note: The content of a NODE_CDATA node and the comment string of a NODE_COMMENT node are considered names.

Method: get_node_offset() → int
Returns the byte offset of the current node from the beginning of the file or buffer.

Method: get_node_type() → NodeType
Returns the type of the current node.

Method: has_attribute(name: String) → bool
Returns true if the current element has an attribute with the specified name.

Method: is_empty() → bool
Returns true if the current element is empty, e.g., <element />.

Method: open(file: String) → Error
Opens an XML file for parsing. Returns an error code.

Method: open_buffer(buffer: PackedByteArray) → Error
Opens an XML raw buffer for parsing. Returns an error code.

Method: read() → Error
Parses the next node in the file. Returns an error code.

Method: seek(position: int) → Error
Moves the buffer cursor to a specific offset and reads the next node. Returns an error code.

Method: skip_section() → void
Skips the current section. If the current node contains inner nodes, they are ignored and the cursor moves to the closing of the current element.